This paper is about object detection using deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a dual reward setting, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for adaptively selecting the spatial resolution of images, which involves making decisions based on the content of the image, a task that is often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential applications of this method in remote sensing, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) and data compression (cs.DC).
